# Blue Affiliate

Affiliate dashboard for Blue Car Rental built with Next.js 16, React 19, Tailwind CSS 4, and shadcn/ui (base-vega style).

## Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 16 (App Router, RSC enabled)
- **UI:** shadcn/ui (base-vega style) + Base UI React + Lucide icons
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS 4 with CSS variables for theming
- **Font:** Host Grotesk (via `next/font/google`, variable `--font-host-grotesk`)
- **Linting/Formatting:** Biome (`npm run lint` / `npm run format`)
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode)

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── app/              # Next.js App Router (layout, pages, globals.css)
├── components/       # App-level components (Sidebar, Navbar, StatsGrid, etc.)
│   └── ui/           # shadcn/ui primitives (button, tabs, accordion, etc.)
├── lib/              # Utilities (cn helper via clsx + tailwind-merge)
└── hooks/            # Custom React hooks
```

Path alias: `@/*` maps to `./src/*`

## Component Conventions

- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Components in `src/components/` use PascalCase filenames
- shadcn/ui primitives live in `src/components/ui/` (lowercase filenames)
- Prefer existing shadcn/ui components before creating new ones
- Icons use the custom `<IconComponent>` wrapper or Lucide directly

## Tailwind Class Discipline

- **Do NOT add Tailwind classes that match the browser/Tailwind default** — only add a class when it changes something.
- `text-base` (16px) is the default font size; do not write it unless explicitly overriding a non-default size set by a parent or ancestor. The same applies to `font-normal`, `text-left`, `leading-normal`, `block` on block-level elements, `static` positioning, etc.
- Before adding any utility class, ask: "Would removing this class change the rendered output?" If no, leave it out.

## Design Tokens

Before adding any styles, check `src/app/globals.css` and use existing CSS variables via Tailwind classes instead of hardcoded values.

Available variables (use as Tailwind classes):
- Colors: `bg-background`, `bg-foreground`, `bg-card`, `bg-card-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `bg-muted`, `bg-accent`, `bg-border`, `bg-input`, `bg-ring`, `bg-destructive`
- Text: `text-foreground`, `text-card-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `text-primary`, `text-secondary`, `text-accent-foreground`
- Border: `border-border`, `border-input`, `border-light-gray`
- Custom theme: `bg-light-gray`, `text-primary` (#155dfc), `text-secondary` (#fd6112)
- Radius: `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl`, `rounded-2xl`, `rounded-3xl`, `rounded-4xl`

| Token              | Light Value   | Usage                     |
|--------------------|---------------|---------------------------|
| `primary`          | `#155dfc`     | Brand blue, CTAs          |
| `secondary`        | `#fd6112`     | Accent orange, highlights |
| `light-gray`       | `#dcdcdc`     | Borders, dividers         |
| `background`       | `#f8f8f8`     | Page background           |
| `foreground`       | `#121212`     | Primary text              |
| `card`             | white         | Card backgrounds          |
| `card-foreground`  | `#101828`     | Card text                 |
| `muted-foreground` | `#4a5565`     | Secondary/muted text      |

Never use arbitrary color values like `bg-[#ffffff]` or `text-[#4a5565]` when a semantic variable exists.
If a new color is needed, add it to the `@theme` block in `globals.css` rather than using arbitrary values.

## Line Height

Use the combined `text-{size}/{leading}` syntax instead of separate `leading-*` classes:
- `text-sm/5` instead of `text-sm leading-5`
- `text-base/7` instead of `text-base leading-7`

Do **not** add a line-height modifier if it matches the Tailwind default for that text size:

| Class       | Default leading (omit if using this) |
|-------------|--------------------------------------|
| `text-xs`   | `4` (1rem)                           |
| `text-sm`   | `5` (1.25rem)                        |
| `text-base` | `6` (1.5rem)                         |
| `text-lg`   | `7` (1.75rem)                        |
| `text-xl`   | `7` (1.75rem)                        |
| `text-2xl`  | `8` (2rem)                           |

Example: `text-sm` already implies `leading-5`, so `text-sm leading-5` must be written as just `text-sm`.

## Code Formatting

All code must be formatted according to the project formatter defined in `.zed/settings.json`.
The project uses **Biome** (`biome format`) for TypeScript, JavaScript, and TSX files.

After writing or editing any file, format it with:
```
biome format --write <file_path>
```

Do not hardcode formatting rules here — Biome is the source of truth for style (indentation, quotes, trailing commas, etc.).

## Figma-to-Code Workflow

When given a Figma URL or asked to implement a design, follow these steps:

### 1. Understand the Design
- Use `get_screenshot` first to see the full visual design
- Use `get_metadata` to discover page structure or find specific frames
- Use `get_variable_defs` to understand the design token system

### 2. Extract Details
- Use `get_design_context` on the specific frame/component — this is the primary tool
- For nested layouts, call `get_design_context` on individual child components
- Always pass `clientLanguages: "typescript,html,css"` and `clientFrameworks: "react,next"`

### 3. Implement
- Map Figma values to existing Tailwind theme tokens (see Design Tokens above)
- Reuse existing shadcn/ui components from `src/components/ui/`
- Figma auto-layout → Tailwind Flexbox: `layoutMode` → `flex-row`/`flex-col`, `itemSpacing` → `gap-*`, `padding` → `p-*`
- Match Figma spacing to Tailwind's 4px-base scale (8px → `2`, 16px → `4`, 24px → `6`)

### 4. Verify
- Use `get_screenshot` again and visually compare against your implementation
- Check exact values with `get_design_context` if anything looks off
- Confirm semantic tokens are used, not raw values

### Figma Token Mapping
- Blue brand color → `primary` (`bg-primary`, `text-primary`)
- Orange accent → `secondary` (`bg-secondary`, `text-secondary`)
- Light border gray → `light-gray` (`border-light-gray`)
- Background → `background` (`bg-background`)
- Body text → `foreground` (`text-foreground`)
- Muted text → `muted-foreground` (`text-muted-foreground`)
- Card surfaces → `card` / `card-foreground`

### Common Pitfalls
- Do NOT skip the screenshot step — always look at the design visually first
- Do NOT call `get_design_context` on entire pages — target specific frames
- Do NOT hardcode hex colors — map to CSS custom properties
- Do NOT over-nest just because Figma's layer tree is deep — flatten where sensible
- If a Figma component has variants (hover, disabled, sizes), implement all states
